:HELP   NAME=OPTIONS.Program Options
:XH3.Program Options
:P.Program options are entered in front of any entry in the list or on the
entry line at the top of the list.
:P.This program includes the following options.
:UL.
:LI.:HP2.1=Select:EHP2.
Option 1 is generally used for add on maintenance screens or select when
prompting. The options are included in blue at the top of the list. The mode
is displayed in the upper left hand corner below the date.
:LI.:HP2.1=Add:EHP2.
Option 1 is generally used for add on maintenance screens or select when
prompting. The options are included in blue at the top of the list. The mode
is displayed in the upper left hand corner below the date.
:LI.:HP2.2=Update:EHP2.
Option 2 is used to update an entry in a list. It goes to the detail screen
for whatever type of entry is being listed.
:LI.:HP2.3=Copy:EHP2.
Option 3 is used to copy an entry in a list. It goes to the detail screen
for the type of entry in the list. The detail screen will be in copy
mode. Copy mode allows a new entry to be created with most of the same values
as the entry being copied.
:LI.:HP2.4=Deactivate:EHP2.
Option 4 deactivates an entry in list. Deactivating an entry does not delete
it. It just flags it as inactive. Most list screens hide inactive entries
by default. Inactive entries are also excluded from most reports by
default. Inactive entries can be reactivated if needed.
:LI.:HP2.5=View:EHP2.
Option 5 is used on list screens to view details about an entry in the
list. It opens the detail screen for the type of entry in the list. The
detail screen is opened in view only mode.
:LI.:HP2.13=Reactivate:EHP2.
Option 13 is used to reactivate inactive entries in a list. By default list
screens hide inactive entries. F11 is normally used to toggle between viewing
and hiding inactive entries.
:EUL.
:EHELP.
