:HELP   NAME='SCHVAL'.Search
:XH3.Search
:p.The search field is used on most list screens. It allows for a generic
search over all columns in the list.
:p.For example, on a vendor list screen, entering TX and Comp in the search
field will show any vendor that has TX in either the name or address, or any
other field for that matter. And also, has the letters comp in any of the
columns. This allows for a quick filter by state and name. However, since it
searches all fields, it will find entries with TX in the name as well. This
does not happen much with TX, but if searching for California, CA, you will
get a lot of entries that CA in the name, not just in the address.
:p.The search also handle quoted strings using double quotes. Entering a value
in double quotes will ensure that the value is found exactly as entered. For
example, if the search string is AMERICAN CAST, the list will include vendors
AMERICAN CASTING and AMERICAN SPINCAST, because both have both words in the
search term. If you only wanted to find AMERICAN CASTING, a search term of
"AMERICAN CAST" can be entered. This will only find vendors with the two words
next to each other, including the space. With this search term AMERICAN
CASTINGS would show up, but AMERICAN SPINCAST would not.
:P.Screen: DCTSEGF1 Field: SCHVAL
Type: CHAR(40)
Location: (4,9)
:EHELP.
