:HELP   NAME='ACVDES'.Active
:XH3.Active
:p.The active field is used to designate a record as active or inactive. The
field is used on many screens throughout the system.
:p.Many list screens
hide inactive records by default, F11 normally toggles between showing them
or not. On list screens option 13 generally reactivates an entry.
:p.On detail screens the active field is normally displayed in the upper
right corner. It designates the status of the entry, either active or
inactive.
:p.On report prompt screens the active field is generally used as a filter
to include or exclude inactive entries from the report.
:p.On filter screens it is used as a filter. The value is toggled on the
list screen using the F11 function, but it can be manually changed on the
filter screen as well.
:P.Screen: DCTSEGF1 Field: ACVDES
Type: CHAR(10)
Location: (7,50)
:EHELP.
